      <body>
         <div>
            <pb facs="#facs_1" n="TLx-0020_p001.jpg" xml:id="img_0001" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/TLx-0020_p001.jpg"/>
            <p facs="#facs_1_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/><date when="15 July 1959">JUL 15 1959</date>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/><rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">RELIGION</rs>, <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">THE ARTS</rs> AND <rs type="keyword" ref="#Science">THE SCIENCES</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/><rs type="keyword" ref="#Humanities">Humanities</rs> 127a
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/><rs type="keyword" ref="#Theology">Theology</rs> 185a
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/><rs type="person" key="Tillich, Paul">Prof. Paul Tillich</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>Tues. and Thurs., 11-12, (Sat.)
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>Assistant--<rs type="person" key="Kimball, Robert">Mr. Robert Kimball</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>Office hours by appointment. Phone Secretary, <rs type="person" key="Leonard, Grace">Mrs. Grace Leonard</rs>, UN. 8-7600, Ext. 769
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>The required work for this semester course will consist of:
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>A minimum of 2800 pages of outside reading. The starred selections are
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>required and will be covered on the final examination. The remainder (ca. 800 pp.)
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>of the reading may be selected at the discretion of the student.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>A final examination. At the time of the examination the student should submit
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_14" n="N014"/>an annotated bibliography of the reading done during the semester.
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_1_r_27">
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l" n="N001"/>BIBLIOGRAPHY
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_13" n="N002"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">General material</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_20" n="N003"/><rs type="person" key="Buber, Martin">Buber, Martin</rs>--*The Eclipse of God
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_27" n="N004"/>*I and Thou
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_34" n="N005"/><rs type="person" key="Brunner, Emil">Brunner, Emil</rs>--Christianity and Civilization
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_41" n="N006"/><rs type="person" key="Eliot, T.S.">Eliot, T. S.-</rs>-Notes on the Definition of Culture
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_48" n="N007"/><rs type="person" key="Frank, Erich">Frank, Erich</rs>--*Philosophical Understanding and Religious Truth
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_55" n="N008"/><rs type="person" key="Jaspers, Karl">Jaspers, Karl</rs>--Man in the Modern Age
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_62" n="N009"/><rs type="person" key="Kroner, Richard">Kroner, Richard</rs>--Culture and Faith
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_69" n="N010"/><rs type="person" key="Niebuhr, Richard H.">Niebuhr, H. Richard</rs>--*Christ and Culture
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_76" n="N011"/>The Meaning of Revelation
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_83" n="N012"/><rs type="person" key="Otto, Rudolf">Otto, Rudolf</rs>--The Idea of the Holy
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_90" n="N013"/><rs type="person" key="Randall, John H.">Randall, John H.</rs>--The Making of the Modern Mind
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_97" n="N014"/><rs type="person" key="Schleiermacher, Friedrich">Schleiermacher, F.</rs>--*On Religion
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_104" n="N015"/><rs type="person" key="Tillich, Paul">Tillich, Paul</rs>--The Protestant Era
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_111" n="N016"/>The Religious Situation
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_118" n="N017"/>*Theology of Culture
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_125" n="N018"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;"><rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">Religion</rs> and <rs type="keyword" ref="#Language">Language</rs></hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_132" n="N019"/><rs type="person" key="Buber, Martin">Buber, Martin</rs>--Between Man and Man
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_139" n="N020"/><rs type="person" key="Bultmann, Rudolf">Bultmann, Rudolf</rs>--*Kerygma and Myth (The opening essay by <rs type="person" key="Bultmann, Rudolf">Bultmann</rs>)
