               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_230" n="N033"/><rs type="person" key="Stern, Karl">Stern, Karl</rs>--The Third Revolution
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_237" n="N034"/><rs type="person" key="Tillich, Paul">Tillich, Paul</rs>--The Courage to Be
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_244" n="N035"/>Love, Power and Justice
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_251" n="N036"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;"><rs type="keyword" ref="#Religion">Religion</rs> and <rs type="keyword" ref="#Arts">the Arts</rs></hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_258" n="N037"/><rs type="person" key="Ferguson, Francis">Fergusson, Francis</rs>--The Idea of a Theatre
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_265" n="N038"/><rs type="person" key="Goddard, Harold">Goddard, Harold</rs>--The Meaning of Shakespeare
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_272" n="N039"/><rs type="person" key="Maritain, Jacques">Maritain, Jacques</rs>--Creative Intuition in Art and Poetry
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_279" n="N040"/><rs type="person" key="Michalson, Carl">Michalson, Carl</rs>--Christianity and the Existentialists
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_286" n="N041"/><rs type="person" key="Ortega y Gasset, ">Ortega y Gasset</rs>--*The Dehumanization of Art
            </p>
